<strong>2</strong> = The prices in an order are saved with 2 decimal places The indirect result of this setting is that the price of a single variation is rounded. The sums and totals of an order are then calculated based on the rounded price of a single variation.<br>
<strong>4</strong> = The prices in an order are saved with 4 decimal places. Selecting 4 decimal places has the effect that the sum of an order item is rounded by default. The sums are saved with 4 decimal places, but further calculation is carried out with sums that are rounded to two decimal places. If you do not want that the sums are rounded by default, you need to additionally activate the setting <strong>Round totals only</strong>.</p></td>
</tr>
